        "contact": {
          "url": "https://github.com/yeo/ec2.shop"
        },
        "description": "A simple and fast API to get Amazon EC2 instance pricing right from your terminal. Supports filtering and sorting by various attributes like memory, CPU, price, and spot price. Provides up-to-date pricing data for on-demand and spot instances, refreshed every 2.5 minutes.",
        "license": {
          "name": "MIT",
          "url": "https://github.com/yeo/ec2.shop/blob/master/LICENSE"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://ec2.shop"
          }
        ],
        "title": "EC2 Shop API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Query Amazon EC2 instance pricing and specs from the command line, with filters and sorting",
        "homepage": "https://ec2.shop",
        "docs_url": "https://github.com/yeo/ec2.shop",
        "license_short": "MIT licensed; community-run service by [yeo](https://github.com/yeo).",
        "license_md": "- The [ec2.shop source](https://github.com/yeo/ec2.shop) is released under the MIT licence.\n- The service is community-run by [yeo](https://github.com/yeo) and is not affiliated with AWS.\n- Underlying pricing data is sourced from AWS's published pricing; consult AWS for authoritative figures before billing decisions.",
        "about_md": "[ec2.shop](https://ec2.shop) is a small, community-run service that turns AWS EC2 pricing into a quick command-line lookup. It is built and maintained by [yeo](https://github.com/yeo) and is designed to be hit with `curl` from a terminal, returning either a human-readable text table or JSON.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n- Instance type, memory, vCPUs, storage, and network specs\n- On-demand hourly cost and a derived monthly price\n- Spot price (string field; may be `\"NA\"` when unavailable)\n- Filtering by instance family, features (e.g. `ssd`, `gpu`), or comparison expressions like `mem>=32,cpu<=4`\n- Sorting by any field with `+`/`-` prefix (for example `sort=-price`)\n- Region selection across 40+ AWS regions\n\nOperational notes: the default response is a text table; pass `Accept: json` or append `?json` for a JSON body. Spot prices are refreshed roughly every 2.5 minutes; on-demand pricing tracks AWS's published pricing pages. No authentication is required and no published rate limits are documented — please be considerate of the service.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "get_instance_pricing": "Lookup of EC2 instance specs and pricing (on-demand hourly, derived monthly, and spot) for a chosen AWS region, served from the root path `/` with optional `filter`, `sort`, and `region` query parameters."
        },
